title: Overlapping UI Elements on Windows
description: Describe the bug Overlapping UI Elements by default due to unexpanded window. The quicksend toggle and the number overlap.  To reproduce 1. Open localsend in windows on a screen that's not that big 2. Observe the overlapping UI elements  Expected behavior The UI elements should not overlap  Screenshots ![image](https://github.com/localsend/localsend/assets/85837722/eb139f0f-0a39-49ee-ab76-382be9b8ccdf) https://github.com/localsend/localsend/assets/85837722/da5bf3f9-95e0-467c-8897-0b44dc290155  Desktop (please complete the following information) -Windows 11 -Version 23H2  Smartphone (please complete the following information) _No response_  Additional context _No response_

title: Bug report: `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` when sharing text via link
description: Describe the bug When I try to share text via a link, when I try to open the "file" that contains the text, there is an exception and I get an `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` error. See log below.  To reproduce 1. Open the app (v1.15.4 and in the latest commit too) in macOS (not tested on other systems) 2. Click the "Text" button and type something and confirm 3. Click on "Send mode" and select "Share via link" 4. Open the link in the browser 5. You see something like this: ![CleanShot 2024-09-11 at 02 01 38@2x](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/58240d09-86a8-4967-b838-8936f87422e5) 7. Try opening 8. `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` error  Expected behavior No error  Screenshots _No response_  Desktop (please complete the following information) macOS 14.6.1, localsend 1.15.4  Smartphone (please complete the following information) - text_for_topic_modeling: Bug report: `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` when sharing text via link  Describe the bug When I try to share text via a link, when I try to open the "file" that contains the text, there is an exception and I get an `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` error. See log below.  To reproduce 1. Open the app (v1.15.4 and in the latest commit too) in macOS (not tested on other systems) 2. Click the "Text" button and type something and confirm 3. Click on "Send mode" and select "Share via link" 4. Open the link in the browser 5. You see something like this: ![CleanShot 2024-09-11 at 02 01 38@2x](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/58240d09-86a8-4967-b838-8936f87422e5) 7. Try opening 8. `ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE` error  Expected behavior No error  Screenshots _No response_  Desktop (please complete the following information) macOS 14.6.1, localsend 1.15.4  Smartphone (please complete the following information) - title: Tray area icons won't disappear
description: Describe the bug On the Windows system, after closing LocalSend, the tray icon is still displayed there, and the mouse pointer will disappear only when it is swept over it, otherwise it will always exist. Although this problem does not affect the use, you need to move the mouse pointer to the tray area every time you close LocalSend, and if you forget to do this, a row of LocalSend icons will appear in the tray area after many times  To reproduce every time  Expected behavior After closing the program, the LocalSend icon in the tray area will not disappear automatically  Screenshots ![ - 1 - 53-045](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48204825/224467640-8a1e2e7e-ffb7-4912-ac8b-f72537f9ceed.png)  Desktop (please complete the following information) _No response_  Smartphone (please complete the following information) _No response_  Additional context _No response_

title: Bug report: Animations default-enabled on Android even if disabled system-wide
description: Describe the bug LocalSend Android unfortunately ignores system animation settings and upon first launch enables its own animations in any case.  To reproduce 1. Enable _Developer options_ 2. Disable animations in _Developer options_ 3. Run _LocalSend_ **for the first time** 4. In its settings, observe _Animations_ toggle being **enabled**  Expected behavior The _Animations_ toggle is never being enabled on its own, especially not by default. Additionally it could be greyed-out if all animations are disabled system-wide.
